  <description type="morphology">Shrubs, 50–150 cm. Stems erect, sparsely puberulent. Petioles 1–4 mm. Leaf blades deltate to deltate-lanceolate or ovate-lanceolate, 3–7 × 1–4 cm, margins serrate to dentate (abaxial faces reticulate-veiny with raised whitish, secondary veins, minutely gland-dotted). Heads usually in 3s, sometimes borne singly. Peduncles 0 or 2–8(–12) mm. Involucres turbinate to campanulate, 5–7 mm. Phyllaries in 4–5 series, apices of the inner appressed, acute (not petaloid or expanded). Corollas pale blue or white.</description>
  <description type="phenology">Flowering Oct–Dec.</description>
  <description type="habitat">Dry limestone hills in oak woodlands, talus;</description>
  <description type="elevation">1000–1800 m;</description>
  <description type="distribution">Tex.; Mexico (Coahuila, Nuevo León, San Luis Potosí).</description>
